  "aboutText": "Monstera standleyana 'Albo Variegated' is a striking variegated cultivar derived from the species native to the tropical lowland rainforests of southern Mexico and Central America. Unlike many other members of the genus, this plant maintains its narrow, entire, elliptic-lanceolate leaf shape throughout its maturity, never developing the fenestrations typical of its relatives. It is highly valued by collectors for its dramatic white sectoral and splash variegation that contrasts beautifully against its deep, glossy green foliage. In nature, the species functions as an epiphyte or hemiepiphyte, utilizing its aerial roots to anchor itself to trees in shaded, humid understory conditions.",
